      <hr>
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <p>One or more authentication codes indicating that the record, existing in a national
         database, has been reviewed in a specific way. The codes are associated with
         specifically designated authentication agencies.      </p>
      <hr>
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> INDICATORS
      </h4>
      <ul>
         <li>Both indicator positions are undefined; each contains a blank (#).</li>
      </ul>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> SUBFIELD CODES
      </h4>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$a - Authentication code</strong> 
        <div class="description">If more than one code is applicable, the subfield is repeated. Code from: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/standards/valuelist/marcauthen.html">MARC Authentication Action Code List</a></em>.
        </div>
   </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Capitalization</strong> - All codes are recorded in lowercase alphabetic characters.
      </div>
